# Windows Task Scheduler

Start → Task Scheduler
  Create Basic Task
    Name: E-REDES Automatic Data Refresh
      Trigger: Daily → choose time (Example: 03:00)
        Action: Start a Program
          Program: python
            Arguments: C:\projects\eredes\eredes_ingest.py (example)
              Start In: C:\projects\eredes (example)
                Save

# Power BI Connection

Get Data → SQL Server
  Enter: 
    Server_ localhost\SQLEXPRESS (or your real server)
    Database_ EnergiaEredes (or your real database)
      Connection mode:
        Import or DirectQuery (depending on your needs)

# Power BI Authentication

  Select:
    Database Authentication
    Username: EredesUser
    Password: PasswordStrong_123!

  Check:
    Encrypt Connection = Yes
    Click Connect.

  Then choose tables such as:
    raw_eredes_national_consumption
    raw_eredes_substation_load
    raw_eredes_municipal_consumption
